James L. Pavitt: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 3:18 AM ET
Aerospace and Defense

Company Overview of Patriot Defense Group, LLC



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
James L. Pavitt  Strategic Advisor, Patriot Defense Group, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships71--
Background

		Mr. James L. Pavitt serves as a Strategic Advisor at Patriot Defense Group, LLC. Mr. Pavitt is a Principal of Scowcroft Group. He is a Co-Owner and President of JLP Associates. He was an Executive Partner at Torch Hill Investment Partners, L.L.C. specializing in intelligence. He provides strategic advice and risk assessments to clients in the fields of homeland security, counterterrorism, financial services, defense and information technology at Scowcroft Group. He has ... more than 30 years of experience in the Intelligence Community, with proven expertise in homeland security, counterterrorism, financial services, defense and information technology. Given his career, Mr. Pavitt is a nationally recognized expert of intelligence and counter-terrorism. He retired as Deputy Director for Operations of CIA for Operations after five years in that position. He managed the agency's globally deployed personnel and nearly half of its multibillion- dollar budget. He also served as the Head of America's Clandestine Service, leading the CIA's operational response to the attacks of September 11, 2001. As Chief of the CIA's Counterproliferation Division, he managed and directed intelligence operations against Global Proliferation Networks. Mr. Pavitt was a career CIA officer with the Clandestine Service and served as Special Assistant to the President on the National Security Council staff responsible for intelligence matters. From 1990 to 1993, he served as Senior Intelligence Advisor on the National Security Council team for President George H.W. Bush. Early in his career, he served as a Legislative Assistant in the U.S. House of Representatives. He has been an Outside Director of CACI International Inc. since August 1, 2008. He serves as member of Advisory Board of Olton Solutions, Ltd. He also serves on the Board of Directors of the Patriot Defense Group, LLC. He served as a Director of Advanced Blast Protection since August 20, 2008 and CUB Energy Inc. from May 30, 2013 to June 2013. Mr. Pavitt is a recipient of the CIA's Distinguished Intelligence Medal for his superior work in these capacities. He received a B.A. in History from the University of Missouri and was a National Defense Education Act Fellow at Clark University.Read Full Background




Corporate Headquarters
151 Southhall LaneMaitland, Florida 32751United StatesPhone: 407-539-2975Fax: 407-628-1508
